{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aadc7709-803f-4972-817a-b7915aa6e4c0","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Additional steps:**\n- Update NuGet packages (especially `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` and `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API changes.\n- Run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad4a8c30-bf38-4447-a31c-092df972062e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search files since they described their setup.","outputTokens":295,"requestId":"C434:16D25D:1D35814:210CB09:6A07C937"},"id":"46900926-c565-42ca-b5b2-d2209b4e4fa2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:32:46.074Z","parentId":"71c2e80c-140a-4256-bbae-47f790dae260"}
